-- BUZZ-BlackRock highlights increased volatility in 2015 outlook
-- 
-- Tue Dec 09, 2014 12:53PM EST
-- None



Dec 9 (Reuters) -    ** BlackRock says investors should consider hedging against downside risk on expected return to normal volatility in 2015

** Sees divergent monetary policies as key theme, tightening in U.S. and U.K. due to growth and improving labor markets  ** Sees Fed tightening, "but only at gentle pace"  ** Sees rising U.S. dollar as key financial market trend  ** Russ Koesterich, global chief investment strategist, favors cyclical sectors like technology and some financial services companies over traditionally defensive sectors like utilities and consumer staples